WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
PDF Solutions in SAP, connecting the shop floor to the top floor.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:11.000
Every yield point, material choice, and cycle hour on the shop floor ultimately lands in finance.

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:16.000
The question is, can your business see and act on that linkage in time?

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:27.000
Semiconductor manufacturing spans thousands of tightly sequenced steps across hundreds of tools over many months, but ERP systems only capture a summarized view of that complexity.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:35.000
In reality, data lives in many different places across equipment, MES, manufacturing data repositories, test systems, and the supply chain.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:45.000
Because these signals are not connected, ERP receives only fragments, making it difficult to see and act on the true financial impact of shop-floor activity.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:51.000
PDF Solutions and SAP partner to bring financial and operational data together.

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:58.000
This allows manufacturers to deploy proven use cases quickly and realize return on investment from day one.

00:00:58.000 --> 01:11.000
At the center is Sapience Manufacturing Hub, a unified interface and centralized operational data layer that connects any MES, equipment source, or factory system with SAP S/4HANA.

01:11.000 --> 01:20.000
By bringing this manufacturing data together, SMH creates a consistent, standardized operational foundation for SAP S/4HANA.

01:20.000 --> 01:26.000
SMH is an enterprise integration platform that connects factory systems to SAP.

01:26.000 --> 01:36.000
It standardizes events from MES and equipment, applies semantic rules, and registers the right milestones back into SAP S/4HANA in a finance-ready format.

01:36.000 --> 01:43.000
ERP and MES operate at different levels of granularity, and manufacturing data often comes from multiple sources.

01:43.000 --> 01:52.000
SMH reconciles these differences and aggregates events into a single, consistent source of truth that flows cleanly into SAP.

01:52.000 --> 01:59.000
Semiconductor lots do not move in a straight line.

01:59.000 --> 02:09.000
They often split, merge, or rework as they travel through the fab, and SMH keeps SAP production orders, batches, and confirmations consistent even when manufacturing paths diverge.

02:09.000 --> 02:17.000
Here is how this works in practice. SAP S/4HANA generates a production order that is ready to be consumed on the shop floor.

02:17.000 --> 02:27.000
SMH picks up that order, creates the corresponding manufacturing lot, and routes the right operational data to MES as production begins.

02:27.000 --> 02:35.000
As production progresses, SMH captures key events from MES and aggregates thousands of detailed steps into clean milestone updates.

02:35.000 --> 02:45.000
These routes are configured with reusable components, ensuring data flows into SAP in a consistent, finance-ready format.

02:45.000 --> 02:54.000
Using Sapience Manufacturing Hub, manufacturers reduce interface build and maintenance costs, accelerate deployments, and achieve tighter traceability and throughput.

02:54.000 --> 03:09.000
SMH provides a unified, standardized source of manufacturing data across factory systems, ensuring SAP has complete and consistent production data across every site and MES environment.

03:09.000 --> 03:22.000
By bringing this manufacturing data together, SMH creates a consistent foundation for high-value solutions such as product costing, sustainability analytics, lot genealogy, and cost of yield.

03:22.000 --> 03:26.000
Now let’s see how that foundation gets used.